  "prompt": "What happens to the soul after salvation?",
  "response": "Different religious traditions have varying perspectives on what happens to the soul after salvation:\n\n1. Christian perspectives:\n- Eternal life with God in Heaven\n- Freed from sin and in perfect communion with God\n- Transformed and sanctified by God's grace\n- Experiences ongoing spiritual growth and relationship with God\n\n2. Protestant view:\n- Assured of salvation through faith in Jesus Christ\n- Indwelled by the Holy Spirit\n- Promised eternal life and spiritual rewards\n\n3. Catholic view:\n- Continues to grow in holiness\n- May experience purification in Purgatory\n- Ultimately enters Heaven\n\n4. Eastern Orthodox view:\n- Continues spiritual transformation\n- Experiences ongoing theosis (becoming more like God)\n\n5. Evangelical view:\n- Secured in God's salvation\n- Called to live a life of discipleship\n- Promised eternal life and future resurrection\n\nThese perspectives emphasize that salvation is not just a one-time event, but an ongoing spiritual journey involving continued growth, transformation, and relationship with God.\n\nEach theological tradition interprets the details somewhat differently, but generally agrees on the core concept of eternal life and restored relationship with God through salvation.",
